[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Examining socket implementation**\n\nI need to use the public constructor for SocketNode, which reads from the socket input stream and blocks until it gets the header. I also need to create connected sockets and an ObjectOutputStream. Running the node might require doing so in the current thread after writing the event and closing the writer. The SocketNode.run method will loop through readObject until EOF. I need to verify the appender is called and avoid package access issues. I’m considering using public LoggerRepository with LogManager for logging.\n\n**Setting up client connections**\n\nI need to accept a client connection and create a SocketNode right after. The ObjectInputStream constructor in SocketNode waits for the header, so the client has to create and flush the ObjectOutputStream first. For testing, I’ll use a ServerSocket and an Executor. I’m planning to submit a task that accepts the socket and runs the SocketNode. Then, I’ll create a Socket client to write an event and flush it. After the node reads the event and catches EOF, I need to ensure the appender is thread-safe.\n\n**Preparing for SocketNodeTest**\n\nI need to set up a one-to-one connection in the active class, which is SocketNodeTest.java. That sounds good! I might also need to import LogManager to handle logging effectively during the tests. It's important to make sure all necessary imports are in place to avoid any issues later on. I'll check that everything is configured correctly for the class to function as expected. Ensuring everything is streamlined will help with the testing process.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0d3c8d78e21999880169f50da7084881a2af4861a8cf84bbc4\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9Q20AFV59hr3Ar-M8OiYNOxPpiJ4N0kKLOFrBIXYv69IpXjNYSW5dNatAIDOM9nCSRCRuA3HlyaKoJnxOHl2T88JJba1ug1FM1VHWUxdvKi-g2zfL5Zp-J3hMHejvAO88gtsdD-GoqG2egJUnTeOkSK1